On Sat, 2004-11-20 at 11:16, Richard Jones wrote:
> I'm happy to announce that mod_caml 1.3.4 has been released. 

Could I ask people making announcements to please include
two things for the convenience of others:

(1) A short description of what the product actually
does. One line is enough.

(2) State the licence of the software.

Point (1) may help people decide whether to look at your
web page to find out more. It would probably also help
those making databases of available Ocaml software,
such as the Humps and Google.

